stateDiagram-v2
    direction LR

    [*] --> WaitingForPaymentCompleted

    WaitingForPaymentCompleted --> RecordingLedger : PaymentCompleted

    RecordingLedger --> WaitingForLedgerRecorded : RecordLedgerEntry

    WaitingForLedgerRecorded --> CheckingEligibility : LedgerEntryRecorded

    CheckingEligibility --> WaitingForEligibility : CheckPayoutEligibility

    WaitingForEligibility --> ReservingBalance : EligibilityApproved

    %% ------------------------------------------------
    %% Scenario 1
    %% Eligibility rejected
    %% ------------------------------------------------
    WaitingForEligibility --> ReversingLedger : EligibilityDenied

    ReservingBalance --> WaitingForBalanceReserved : ReserveBalance

    %% ------------------------------------------------
    %% Scenario 2
    %% Reservation never succeeded
    %% ------------------------------------------------
    WaitingForBalanceReserved --> ReversingLedger : BalanceReservationFailed

    %% ------------------------------------------------
    %% Reservation completed successfully
    %% ------------------------------------------------
    WaitingForBalanceReserved --> NotifyingMerchant : BalanceReserved

    %% ------------------------------------------------
    %% Scenario 3
    %% Late fraud / compliance decision after reservation
    %% is confirmed (NotifyingMerchant is only reached
    %% once BalanceReserved has occurred)
    %% ------------------------------------------------
    NotifyingMerchant --> ReversingBalance : PaymentFlaggedFraudulent

    NotifyingMerchant --> WaitingForNotification : NotifyMerchant

    WaitingForNotification --> Completed : MerchantNotified

    Completed --> [*]

    %% =================================================
    %% Compensation Flow
    %% =================================================

    ReversingBalance --> ReversingLedger : BalanceReservationReversed

    ReversingLedger --> Reversed : LedgerEntryReversed

    Reversed --> Closed

    Closed --> [*]

    %% =================================================
    %% Notes
    %% =================================================

    note right of WaitingForPaymentCompleted
        Saga instance is created earlier
        and remains idle until the
        PaymentCompleted event arrives.
    end note

    note right of NotifyingMerchant
        Reached only after BalanceReserved,
        so the payment is already
        financially consistent here.
        Notification failures never
        trigger financial compensation.
        Only exceptional post-reservation
        business decisions (for example,
        a late fraud/compliance decision)
        may initiate compensation.
    end note

    note right of WaitingForNotification
        MerchantNotified means the
        Notification Service accepted
        the NotifyMerchant command.
        Webhook delivery, retries,
        exponential backoff,
        Dead Letter Queue processing,
        and replay are handled
        asynchronously by the
        Notification/Webhook subsystem
        and are outside this saga.
    end note

    note right of ReversingLedger
        Compensation is history-aware.
        Only successfully completed
        financial operations are
        compensated, in reverse order.
        If balance reservation never
        succeeded, balance reversal
        is skipped.
    end note

    note right of Reversed
        REVERSED indicates every
        completed financial operation
        has been successfully
        compensated.
        The saga then transitions
        to CLOSED.
    end note